                            <comment id="217078" author="adilger" created="Fri, 22 Dec 2017 09:42:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close old bug that has not been hit in a long time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64253" author="green" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 16:22:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a sign of a deadlock on the ost side where unmount and lazyinit are shoiwng signs of transaction being held open by something and then there&apos;s parallel unmount that they might be racing with (that holds the transaction?) that waits for everything to shut down.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
